'''Franck Perera''' (Born [[21 June]], [[1984]], [[Montpellier]], [[France]]) is a [[race car]] [[driving|driver]]. In [[2006]] Perera drove in the [[GP2 Series]] for the [[DAMS]] team, after four years of racing for the Prema team in junior championships. In 2007 he drove for [[Condor Motorsports]] in the [[Champ Car Atlantic Championship]], scoring three wins and finishing second in the championship behind [[Raphael Matos]].<ref>[http://www.champcaratlantic.com/Results/Standings.asp?latestSeason=2007 Champ Car Atlantic Standings]</ref>  On February 6, 2008, Perera announced that he had signed with [[Conquest Racing]] to compete in the [[Champ Car World Series]] in [[2008 Champ Car World Series Season]] after a successful test with the team.<ref>[http://auto-racing.speedtv.com/article/champ-car-perera-inks-conquest-deal/ Perera Inks Conquest Deal], SpeedTV.com, February 6, 2008</ref> However, shortly thereafter Champ Car and the [[Indy Racing League]] unified, canceling the Champ Car season. It was announced on February 25 that Perera had modified his deal in order to continue with the team in the IRL [[IndyCar Series]].<ref>Lewandowski, Dave. [http://www.indycar.com/news/story.php?story_id=10565 Conquest Racing the first to make move; Perera named], IndyCar.com, February 25, 2008</ref>
